      <conbodydiv class="- topic/bodydiv concept/conbodydiv ">
         <section class="- topic/section ">
            <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
               <hazardstatement conref="../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/high_current_cap-inverter"
                                platform="WxW"
                                class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
                  <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
                     <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
                     <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
                  </messagepanel>
               </hazardstatement>
               <hazardstatement conref="../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/high_current_capacitors"
                                platform="PxW SDC"
                                class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
                  <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
                     <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
                     <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
                  </messagepanel>
               </hazardstatement>
               <p class="- topic/p ">A system check is performed
during the commissioning. Pay special attention to specific steps
that are only valid for some configurations and system types.</p>
               <p otherprops="typeS" class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for single system: </b>The system check is performed for the system. Afterwards it is in <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">normal operation</ph>
                  <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">float charge</ph>, without any load connected.</p>
               <p otherprops="typeD" class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for dual systems: </b>The system check
is performed for one unit at a time, the order of the units does not
matter. Afterwards both units are in normal operation, without any
load connected.</p>
               <p otherprops="typeR" class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant systems: </b>The <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">two first
sections</ph>
                  <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">first section</ph> in the system check
is performed for one unit at a time, <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">starting with unit2</u>. Afterwards <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2 is in standby</u> and <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1 is in <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">normal operation</ph>
                     <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">float charge</ph>
                  </u>, without
any load connected.</p>
            </sectiondiv>
         </section>
         <section id="BatteryOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BF085"
                  platform="PxW SDC"
                  class="- topic/section ">
            <title class="- topic/title ">Battery Operation Check on One Unit</title>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Close the rectifier mains input breaker.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">After about 10 seconds the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>.</p>
                  <note conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/autostart_start-up"
                        class="- topic/note "/>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Lamp test button</b> and check that all LED’s
on the front panel illuminates. </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for one second, if the unit did
not start from the autostart. After a few seconds or if any key is
pressed the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph platform="PxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation
load power ...%</codeph>
                     <codeph platform="SDC" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Float charge load ...%</codeph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant systems with a common
battery: </b>Close the rectifier output switch.</p>
                  <note id="TheOutputTerminalWillBeEnergizedIfT-63CB6F12"
                        type="important"
                        class="- topic/note ">The output terminal will be energized if the system does not have
an output breaker.</note>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 8 key</b> to check the DC voltage.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If the DC voltage is within tolerance, close the battery breaker
and battery protection breaker if applicable. The battery is now connected
to the unit.</p>
                  <note class="- topic/note ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant system with a common
battery: </b>If the system has a common battery protection breaker
it will already be closed when performing the check on <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u>.</note>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 5 key</b> to check the battery current.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 9 key</b> to check that
the inverter output voltage is within tolerance. Check that the green
inverter LED on the mimic diagram is illuminated.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Open the rectifier mains input breaker. Check that the unit
changes to battery operation, and that the green battery LED on the
mimic diagram is illuminated. The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> will show <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Batt. operation time ...min</codeph>.</p>
                  <note class="- topic/note "> The remaining runtime
will only be shown if advanced battery monitor is installed.</note>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Let the unit be in battery operation for 30 seconds to check
that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Battery operation</b> indication activates on the alarm
panel.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Close the rectifier mains input breaker. Check that the unit
changes to <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">normal operation</ph>
                     <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">float charge</ph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant systems with individual
batteries, orsingle systems with a rectifier output
switch: </b>Close the rectifier output switch.</p>
                  <note conref="#./TheOutputTerminalWillBeEnergizedIfT-63CB6F12"
                        type="-dita-use-conref-target"
                        class="- topic/note "/>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm the alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> in redundant systems
with individual batteries: </b>Open the battery breaker.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u>  in redundant systems: </b>Press both the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> and the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">OFF button</b> at the
same time for two seconds. The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> now shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Continue with the section:<sl platform="PxW" class="- topic/sl ">
                        <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For all systems with bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="#./BypassOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BEEEC"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For single systems without bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_0000388799.dita"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="concept"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For dual systems without bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="#./AdditionalStepsForDualSystems-8EFBDCC3"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For redundant systems without bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="#./AdditionalStepsForRedundantSystems-8EFBDEDE"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     </sl>
                     <sl platform="SDC" class="- topic/sl ">
                        <sli otherprops="typeS" class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For single systems: </b>
                           <xref href="Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_0000388799.dita"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="concept"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli otherprops="typeR" class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For redundant systems: </b>
                           <xref href="#./AdditionalStepsForRedundantSystems-8EFBDEDE"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     </sl>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </section>
      </conbodydiv>
      <conbodydiv class="- topic/bodydiv concept/conbodydiv ">
         <section id="StartUpCheckOnOneUnit-20D8C3C2"
                  platform="WxW"
                  class="- topic/section ">
            <title class="- topic/title ">Start Up Check on One Unit</title>
            <note type="important" class="- topic/note "> The DC
capacitors needs to be charged before the inverter input switch is
closed.</note>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the external source of the DC input power is available.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Charge the DC capacitors:</p>
                  <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Keep the charging/discharging switch it in position 2 (charge)
until the warning LED turns off.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">With the charging/discharging switch still in position 2 (charge),
close the inverter input switch. If not possible, release the charging/discharging
switch and quickly close the inverter input switch.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Release the charging/discharging switch.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ol>
                  <note conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/autostart_start-up"
                        class="- topic/note "/>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Lamp test button</b> and check that all LED’s
on the front panel illuminates. </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for one second, if the unit did
not start from the autostart. After a few seconds or if any key is
pressed the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation load power
...%</codeph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 8 key</b> to check the DC voltage.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 5 key</b> to check the DC current.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 9 key</b> to check that the inverter output
voltage is within tolerance. Check that the green inverter LED on
the mimic diagram is illuminated.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm the alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Continue with the section:<sl class="- topic/sl ">
                        <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For all systems with bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="#./BypassOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BEEEC"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For single systems without bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_0000388799.dita"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="concept"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For dual systems without bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="#./AdditionalStepsForDualSystems-8EFBDCC3"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                        <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For redundant systems without bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="#./AdditionalStepsForRedundantSystems-8EFBDEDE"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     </sl>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </section>
      </conbodydiv>
      <section id="BypassOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BEEEC"
               platform="PxW WxW"
               class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Bypass Operation Check on One Unit</title>
         <hazardstatement conref="../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/output_energized"
                          class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <note class="- topic/note ">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For systems with a manual bypass switch: </b>Check the position of the manual bypass switch. It should be in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> except if the check is performed on <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u> in a
redundant system with a common manual bypass switch.</note>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Close the bypass mains input breaker. </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p "> If applicable, close the bypass isolation switch.</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="generalM 3pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="tempExclude" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only
for 3-position manual bypass switch: </b>Turn the manual bypass switch
to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> position. <note class="- topic/note ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant systems with
common manual bypass: </b>The manual bypass switch will already be
in the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> position when performing the check for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u>.</note>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="2pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for 2-position manual bypass switch: </b>Close the EN input switch.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the yellow inverter LED on the mimic diagram is
illuminated, indicating that the inverter is synchronized with the
bypass mains.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the green LED before the static switch EN (upstream)
on the mimic diagram is illuminated, indicating that the bypass mains
is available and within tolerance.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to bypass operation:<ol conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Switch-to-bypass"
                      class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li class="- topic/li "/>
                  </ol>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch back to normal operation:</p>
               <ol conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Switch-to-normal"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation
load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> in redundant systems: </b>Press both
the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> and the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">OFF button</b> at the same time for
two seconds. The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> now shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Continue with the section:<sl class="- topic/sl ">
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For single or dual units with manual bypass switch(es): </b>
                        <xref href="#./SetManualBypassSwitchesToAuto-AA6C103D"
                              scope="local"
                              type="section"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For single units without manual bypass switch(es): </b>
                        <xref href="Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_0000388799.dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="concept"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For dual units without manual bypass switch(es): </b>
                        <xref href="#./AdditionalStepsForDualSystems-8EFBDCC3"
                              scope="local"
                              type="section"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For redundant systems: </b>
                        <xref href="#./AdditionalStepsForRedundantSystems-8EFBDEDE"
                              scope="local"
                              type="section"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                  </sl>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </section>
      <section id="AdditionalStepsForRedundantSystems-8EFBDEDE"
               otherprops="typeR"
               class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Additional Steps for Redundant Systems</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Repeat the relevant sections for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u>:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">
                              <xref href="#./BatteryOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BF085"
                                    scope="local"
                                    type="section"
                                    class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">
                              <xref href="#./StartUpCheckOnOneUnit-20D8C3C2"
                                    scope="local"
                                    type="section"
                                    class="- topic/xref "/>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">
                              <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For systems with bypass:</b>
                              <xref href="#./BypassOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BEEEC"
                                    scope="local"
                                    type="section"
                                    class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Repeat the <xref href="#./BatteryOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BF085"
                           scope="local"
                           type="section"
                           class="- topic/xref "/> section for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">redundant communication
cables are</ph>
                     <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">parallel communication cable is</ph> connected according to the specifications in the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Connection Diagram</i>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u>: </b>Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for
one second to restart <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u>.<ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph "> Check that
the yellow inverter LED on the mimic diagrams is illuminated.</ph>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Displays</b> on both units show <codeph platform="PxW WxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation load power ...%</codeph>
                     <codeph platform="SDC" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Float charge load ...%</codeph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Close <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">both</u> output isolation switches.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> in redundant systems
with individual batteries: </b>Close the battery breaker.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check that alarms for the parallel communication
are not active.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Continue with the section <xref href="#./SetManualBypassSwitchesToAuto-AA6C103D"
                           scope="local"
                           type="section"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">After both units are checked and in float charge,
continue with the section <xref href="Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_0000388799.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section id="SetManualBypassSwitchesToAuto-AA6C103D"
               platform="PxW WxW"
               class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Set Manual Bypass Switch(es) to Auto and/or Check Parallel
Communication</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant systems: </b>This procedure
is performed to verify that the parallel communication is working
as intended. Only switch operation from <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u> and check that <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> reacts in the same way.</p>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch the unit to bypass operation:</p>
               <ol conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Switch-to-bypass"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p "> Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant system: </b>Check that <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> also
switched to bypass operation.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the green LED after the inverter (downstream) on
the mimic diagram is illuminated, indicating that the inverter output
is available and within tolerance.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for systems with manual bypass switch(es): </b>If the
inverter output is available and within tolerance, switch the manual
bypass switch(es) to the position <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b>.</p>
               <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">
                  <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant system: </b>A redundant system might have one
or more manual bypass switches. <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Both</u> manual bypass switches
must be switched to <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b>.</note>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch the unit to normal operation:</p>
               <ol conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Switch-to-normal"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p "> Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation
load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for redundant system: </b>Check that <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> also
switched to normal operation.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Continue with the section:<sl class="- topic/sl ">
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For single and redundant systems: </b>
                        <xref href="Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_0000388799.dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="concept"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For dual systems: </b>
                        <xref href="#./AdditionalStepsForDualSystems-8EFBDCC3"
                              scope="local"
                              type="section"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>.</sli>
                  </sl>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </section>
      <section id="AdditionalStepsForDualSystems-8EFBDCC3"
               otherprops="typeD"
               class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Additional Steps for Dual Systems</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Repeat the sections for the other unit in the system, until
all applicable sections are performed and both units are checked:</p>
                  <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <xref href="#./BatteryOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BF085"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <xref href="#./StartUpCheckOnOneUnit-20D8C3C2"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>
                        </p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for systems with bypass: </b>
                           <xref href="#./BypassOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BEEEC"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for systems with manual bypass switches: </b>
                           <xref href="#./SetManualBypassSwitchesToAuto-AA6C103D"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="section"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ol>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">After both units are checked and in normal operation, continue
with the section <xref href="Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_0000388799.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
   </conbody>
